# TESS Program G06197

Title: Identifying Companion Stars Of Close White Dwarf Binaries

PI: Suzuki, Nao - Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory

Type: SMALL

Summary: The White Dwarf binary systems in Milky Way are important resources for two major areas of astrophysics: Gravitational Wave and Type Ia Supernova Cosmology. Thanks to the precise measurement of distances by GAIA satellite, we could identify binary candidates on the Hertzsprung Russell diagram (HR Diagram). We propose to investigate white dwarf binary candidates in the neighborhood of the solar system.
